      "post_id" : 33091899,
      "comment_id" : 70461335,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "Nice idea, but if you put a <code>null</code> value as the second parameter (which defines the class, in which inheritance hierarchy Spring will scan for a class which uses the Annotation), you&#180;ll allway get a <code>null</code> back, according to the implementation."
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 482529,
      "reputation" : 5502,
      "user_id" : 896981,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 100,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/253086bb97bfb344eef07076c103c0fb?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "magiccrafter",
